In Mac:
Get-Help Copy-Item	: 	Provide synopsis, commandlet, Important to learn how we can read the syntax

Copy a file/folder from one place to another:
Copy-Item -Path /Users/javedalam/Documents/Extra/x2.txt .
Copy-Item /Users/javedalam/Documents/Extra/x2.txt /Users/javedalam/Documents/DevOpsLabs/PowerShell/
Copy-Item /Users/javedalam/Documents/Extra/x2.txt -Destination /Users/javedalam/Documents/DevOpsLabs/PowerShell/                                             


List the process in detailed:
Get-Process -Id <ID_NO>				: 	List the process
Stop-Process	<ID_NO>					: 	Stop the running process 
Get-Process powershell                                                                                   

 NPM(K)    PM(M)      WS(M)     CPU(s)     Id  SI ProcessName                                                                                                
 ------    -----      -----     ------     --  -- -----------                                                                                                
      0     0.00      58.31     336.99  13059 425 powershell                                                                                                 
      0     0.00     120.29   1,257.51  13125 453 powershell  

get-help Get-Process -Detailed			: 	Detailed with examples
get-help Get-Process -Full
get-help Get-Process -Examples
get-help Get-Process -Online				:	Online Help
get-help Get-Process -ShowWindow		: 	Open in window


Basic Commandlets:
Clear-Host			:		Clear the screen same as Linux ($ clear)
Get-Process			:		List all process
Stop-Process			: 		Stop the process
Get-Service			:		List the status of services in powershell like running, stopped and so on


